Q.Why normalization?
Answer: 
Reduce
redundancy
inconsistency
update anomalies

Q.Does normalization improve performance?

answer:
Better consistency 
Too many joins can slow reads

Q.Why companies denormalize?

Answer:Faster reads in large-scale systems

Example: analytics,dashboards

Q.Is “more normalization always better?”

Answer:NO
Too much normalization:

many joins
complex queries
slower reads

Q.Difference: 2NF vs 3NF

Answer:
2NF Removes partial dependency

Meaning:
Column should depend on FULL primary key

3NF Removes transitive dependency

Meaning: Non-key columns should depend only on the PRIMARY KEY.

Q.Which is better?

A. Highly normalized DB
B. Denormalized DB

Answer: Depends on:

Read-heavy vs write-heavy system
Performance needs
Data consistency requirements

Normalized DB Better for:

consistency
transactional systems

Denormalized DB Better for:

analytics
dashboards
faster reads
banking/payment systems
